                <p>
                It is important to carefully understand why you choose to study in a particular country. 
				There are several important factors that need to be understood before you take this big step. 
				COSMO IMMIGRATION believes in giving the real picture to students & parents.
				COSMO IMMIGRATION represents institutions across several countries UK, USA, Canada, Australia, New Zealand, Singapore, Ireland, Switzerland, France, Malaysia, Dubai, Germany, Denmark, Spain. All programs are covered from UG,PG to Phd's.
                </p>
                <h3 class='country-heading'>Advantages of studying in Canada</h3>
                <div class="well well-lg">
                	<ul>
                		<li>Canada ranks as the world’s 7th most popular destination for international students.</li>
                		<li>There were 336,497 international students in Canada in 2014, representing an 83% increase since 2008, and an increase of 10% over the previous year.</li>
                		<li>International students made up 11% of the postsecondary student population in Canada in the 2012-2013 academic year.</li>
                		<li>Students from China make up fully one-third (33%) of Canada’s international student population, followed by students from India (12%), South Korea (5.8%), France (5.7%) and Saudi Arabia (4%)</li>
                		<li>Of the 336,497 international students in Canada, 86% are in Ontario, British Columbia or Québec.</li>
                		<li>According to CBIE’s International Student Survey (2015), Engineering, business and the natural and social sciences are the top fields of study of international students in Canada.</li>
                		<li>The top alternate study destinations considered by international students in Canada are the United States, the United Kingdom, and Australia.</li>
                	</ul>
                	<p>With quality and more affordable tuition, safe cities, employment options (both during and after the study period), and as a pathway to Canadian permanent residence, the decision to study in Canada can be one of the most important, and best, decisions made by young people from around the world.
World-class universities and colleges
Canadian universities and colleges located across the country are renowned for their research and innovation. Canada’s higher education institutions are diverse — varying in size, scope, character and breadth of programs. High academic standards and thorough quality controls mean that students may gain a high-quality education that will benefit their careers over the long term. A Canadian degree, diploma or certificate is generally recognized as being equivalent to those obtained from the United States or Commonwealth countries.</p>
                </div>
                <h3 class='country-heading'>The Advantages Of Studying In Australia</h3>
                 <div class="well well-lg">
                 	<p>Australia has the third highest number of international students in the world behind only the United Kingdom and the United States despite having a population of only 23 One of the fastest emerging economies in the World, Australia is also the 3rd most sought after international student destination, especially, for higher education. The country is ranked 10th in U21 Ranking of National Higher Education Systems and placed above Germany and Japan. Having around 50,000 people involved in research and development studies Australia is one of the top research intensive countries with strong research and development capabilities. One of the World’s largest and most diverse research institutions ‘Commonwealth Scientific and Industrial Research Organisation (CSIRO)’ is based in Australia.</p>
                 	<h4>Quality of Education in Australia</h4>
                 	<p>Quality of Education is one of the best reasons to study in Australia. The country is home to over 1,100 institutions and 43 universities of which at least 5 universities are placed under the top 50 universities in the World in QS Top University Ranking every year. The Australian National University and the University of Melbourne are ranked 19th and 42nd in QS Top University Ranking 2016. With over 22,000 courses, Australian universities have a variety of programmes to offer to students from overseas. Whether it is MBA or MIS, Engineering or Tourism, Australian universities have a variety of part-time and full-time study programmes designed according to the student’s requirement and schedule. Australia is also one of the research intensive countries with strong research and development capabilities. This is one of the top reasons to study in Australia. Around 50,000 people in higher education organisations are involved in research and development studies. According to International Student Enrolment Data 2013, there were 526,932 enrolments by full-fee paying international students in Australia on a student visa.</p>
					<h4>Cost of studying and living in Australia</h4>
					<p>Being one of the most prominent destinations to study, Australia is also one of the costliest countries in the World. However, despite of having World’s top universities studying in Australia is economical as compared to universities in USA or UK and it is one of the top reasons to study in Australia. HSBC report says that the average cost per year of study in Australia for international students is AU$42,093 which includes tuition fee and cost of living in Australia and according to Australian National University, minimum cost of study of a graduate degree programs is AU$28,608 at ANU. For cost of living, Department of Immigration and Border Protection insures that a person must have AU$18,610 per year in bank account to manage their living expenses in Australia.</p>
                 </div>
                 <h3 class='country-heading'>The Advantages Of Studying In New Zealand</h3>
                 <div class="well well-lg">
                 	<p>There may be lots of reasons you’re considering New Zealand as your study destination.But naturally you have to be confident about the quality of education on offer. Be reassured. New Zealand schools, universities and institutes are known worldwide for their high standards. You’ll find its qualifications are internationally recognised and welcomed by employers.Around 100,000 international students live and study in New Zealand each year.</p>
                 	<h4>Student visa processing</h4>
                 	<p>New Zealand’s worldwide network of branches processes student visa applications lodged overseas, while its Palmerston North Student Branch processes most foreign fee-paying applications lodged in New Zealand. Reflecting the importance of the international education industry to the New Zealand economy, they  have undertaken various initiatives to improve our processing of the 49,000 student applications received annually in New Zealand. This will particularly improve processing times during the peak processing months of February, March and July, when an average of nearly 10,000 applications are received each month.</p>
                 </div>
